<br>
I would probably like to solo using charmed pets if possible anyway. Charming is fun <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub24.ezboard.com/bnonguild.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chants>Chants</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#333333>(6/15/02 3:08:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub24.ezboard.com/fnonguildfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1554.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Soloing Chanters?</span><hr size=1> Solo with a Chanter is a real challange, while we share the same line of fear with the necro class we really do not have an effective snare. A technique that I use is to Tash pull the MoB (Always have rune and whatever level of beserker strength you have on) it agros you pet attacks then stun like mad. your pet can not tank an exp Mob on its own. If it keeps agro it will die very fast. I will stun, stun, stun... back off cast, jump in and stun some more (dosent hurt to have auto attack on while you stun). This is all very mana intensive and the down time sucks. As far as charmed Mobs I have not done it too much, Charm always seems to break at the worst moment. As for the pet changes they did not effect the Enc pet much (other than the exp change for all pets) the big change is that they will not attack mezed mobs... which I think sucks, as before my pet was smart enough and taunted well enough to break mez on greens that I was killing for faction. It also used to take them out in the order that I mezed, as long as I was hit by the mob prior to mez.<br>
I hope some of this helped. Good luck, Oh and the best combo for Enc fear kiting is you and a ranger.... they make good pets <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
